\fs32\b 7. Sprint 1 Retrospective\b0\par
\fs22 What went well:\par
\fs22 \u8226? Breaking work into small commits made it easy to track progress.\par
\fs22 \u8226? Starting with reducer unit tests reduced risk before adding UI tests.\par
\fs22 \u8226? A simple CI workflow (lint + test + build) gives fast feedback.\par
\par
\fs22 What didn\u8217?t go well:\par
\fs22 \u8226? UI tests initially failed due to ambiguous text matches (prices appear in multiple places).\par
\fs22 \u8226? Test runner failed when there were zero test files (needed at least one test to pass).\par
\par
\fs22 Improvements for Sprint 2 (commit to at least 2):\par
\fs22 1. Scope UI assertions to specific regions (use within(...)) to avoid brittle tests.\par
\fs22 2. Add basic logging/monitoring (structured logs + error boundary) to improve troubleshooting.\par
\fs22 3. Add persistence-focused tests for localStorage rehydration and updates.\par
\par
\fs32\b 8. Sprint 2 Plan\b0\par
\fs22 Sprint Goal: Apply Sprint 1 learnings, improve observability, and deliver the next increment with monitoring/logging and expanded coverage.\par
\par
\fs22 Selected Backlog Items (2\u8211?3 stories):\par
\fs22 1. Basic monitoring/logging for key events (2 SP)\par
\fs22 2. Persist cart across refresh (2 SP) \u8212? add tests to validate safe rehydration\par
\fs22 3. Evidence artifacts for sprint reviews and retrospectives (2 SP)\par
\par
\fs22 Total: 6 SP\par
\par
\fs22 Process Improvements (to apply):\par
\fs22 \u8226? Keep commits small and message scopes clear.\par
\fs22 \u8226? Add tests alongside changes (not at the end).\par
\fs22 \u8226? Ensure CI stays green (fix failures immediately).\par
\par
\fs32\b 9. Sprint 2 Review\b0\par
\fs22 Sprint Goal: Add lightweight monitoring/logging to improve observability of cart + ordering flows and capture runtime errors.\par
\par
\fs22 Delivered:\par
\fs22 \u8226? Client-side event logging for cart and order actions (dev/test only).\par
\fs22 \u8226? Simple in-memory counters (metrics) for key events.\par
\fs22 \u8226? Guarded localStorage read/write with failure signals.\par
\fs22 \u8226? ErrorBoundary + global error handlers for unexpected UI/runtime errors.\par
\par
\fs22 Evidence (references):\par
\fs22 \u8226? CI run on branch: lint + tests pass.\par
\fs22 \u8226? Metrics/logging code: src/observability/*\par
\fs22 \u8226? Tests updated to assert storage read failure metric increments.\par
\par
\fs22 Demo Script:\par
\fs22 1. Add item to cart, increment/decrement quantity, remove item.\par
\fs22 2. Confirm Order, then Start New Order.\par
\fs22 3. Refresh page to confirm cart persistence still works.\par
\par
\fs22 Acceptance Criteria Check:\par
\fs22 \u8226? Observability added without changing normal UX.\par
\fs22 \u8226? Logging does not crash the app if console/storage fails.\par
\fs22 \u8226? CI remains green.\par
\par
\fs32\b 10. Sprint 2 Retrospective\b0\par
\fs22 What went well:\par
\fs22 \u8226? Observability added with minimal surface area and low risk.\par
\fs22 \u8226? Tests and CI stayed green after instrumentation.\par
\par
\fs22 What didn\u8217?t go well:\par
\fs22 \u8226? Need clearer separation between product tests and observability tests as the suite grows.\par
\par
\fs22 Improvements / Action Items:\par
\fs22 \u8226? Add one focused unit test for ErrorBoundary fallback behavior.\par
\fs22 \u8226? Consider a small abstraction for storage access so read/write failures are consistently tracked.\par
